William Blase Named SBC Southwest President And CEO
Company Veteran to Oversee Multi-State Operations
, Texas, San Antonio, Texas, June 2, 2003
SBC Communications Inc. has named William A. Blase Jr. SBC Southwest president and CEO.  Effective immediately, Blase will have leadership responsibility for network and consumer and business sales in the five-state SBC Southwest territory.
Blase, a 24-year veteran of SBC, will oversee SBC Southwest telephone operations providing basic and advanced communications services to tens of millions of customers in Arkansas, Kansas, Missouri, Oklahoma and Texas.
"Bill is a proven telecommunications industry leader who has led several key SBC operations from California to Connecticut," said Edward E. Whitacre Jr., chairman and CEO of SBC.  "Bill will ensure that the SBC Southwest region continues to provide our customers with the innovative telecommunications products they want and need, while providing the best possible customer service experience in a challenging competitive environment."
Blase most recently served as SBC SNET president and CEO, managing wireline services delivery to SBC customers in Connecticut.  His previous SBC positions included serving as president of external affairs for California and Nevada, and managing a number of marketing, external affairs and investor relations teams in the Southwest.
Blase, 48, holds a bachelor's degree in political science from Loyola University, an M.B.A. from the University of Missouri, and a Ph.D. with an emphasis in finance from St. Louis University.
Blase replaces John Stankey, who was named senior executive vice president and CIO of SBC Communications.
SBC Communications Inc. is one of the world's leading data, voice and Internet services providers.  Through its world-class networks, SBC companies provide a full range of voice, data, networking and e-business services, as well as directory advertising and publishing.  A Fortune 30 company, America's leading provider of high-speed DSL Internet Access services, and one of the nation's leading Internet Service Providers, SBC companies currently serve 58 million access lines nationwide.  In addition, SBC companies own 60 percent of America's second largest wireless company, Cingular Wireless, which serves more than 22 million wireless customers.  Internationally, SBC companies have telecommunications investments in 22 countries.













